Error: Error: "Unable To Create Backup: Failed To Connect To FTP Server"

Solution: Step 1: Check your FTP credentials for errors. Make sure you have the correct username, password, IP address and port.

Step 2: Check firewall settings. If you have a firewall enabled, make sure it is not blocking your connection to the FTP server.

Step 3: Check the FTP server status. Ensure that the FTP server is running and accepting connections. You can verify this by testing the connection
